.TH "devm_iio_dmaengine_buffer_alloc" 9 "devm_iio_dmaengine_buffer_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_iio_dmaengine_buffer_alloc \- Resource-managed iio_dmaengine_buffer_alloc()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct iio_buffer *" devm_iio_dmaengine_buffer_alloc
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *channel "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Parent device for the buffer
.IP "channel" 12
DMA channel name, typically "rx".
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This allocates a new IIO buffer which internally uses the DMAengine framework
to perform its transfers. The parent device will be used to request the DMA
channel.

The buffer will be automatically de-allocated once the device gets destroyed.
